The paper deals with polynomial representations of threshold functions and their algorithmic applications, which are topics that are typically studied in computational complexity (cs.CC) and algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also involves geometric algorithms for nearest neighbor problems, which falls under computational geometry (cs.CG). Additionally, the paper discusses probabilistic techniques and lower bounds, which are relevant to discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and network science (cs.NE).
